# Database Migrations Plan

This file defines the first SQLite database structure.

Aim Brain must treat raw imported runs as the source of truth.

Derived stats can be recalculated.

---

## Migration Philosophy

Use small migrations.

Do not create one giant uncontrolled schema.

Recommended first migration files:

```text
src-tauri/migrations/
  001_app_settings.sql
  002_import_pipeline.sql
  003_raw_runs.sql
  004_scenario_matching.sql
  005_benchmark_definitions.sql
  006_analysis_cache.sql
  007_setup_tracking.sql
```

MVP can start with 001-005.

---

## 001_app_settings.sql

Purpose:
- app-level settings
- schema metadata
- feature flags

Tables:

```sql
CREATE TABLE app_settings (
  key TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  value_json TEXT NOT NULL,
  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL
);
```

Examples:
- active_benchmark_definition_id
- preferred_platform
- import_mode
- theme
- telemetry_enabled false by default if telemetry ever exists

---

## 002_import_pipeline.sql

Purpose:
- safe imports
- duplicate prevention
- import reports

Tables:

```sql
CREATE TABLE import_sources (
  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  platform TEXT NOT NULL,
  source_type TEXT NOT NULL,
  display_name TEXT NOT NULL,
  path TEXT,
  enabled INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,
  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,
  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE import_batches (
  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  source_id TEXT,
  platform TEXT NOT NULL,
  status TEXT NOT NULL,
  started_at TEXT NOT NULL,
  completed_at TEXT,
  error_message TEXT,
  imported_count INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
  skipped_count INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
  review_count INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
  FOREIGN KEY (source_id) REFERENCES import_sources(id)
);

CREATE TABLE imported_files (
  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  source_id TEXT,
  file_path TEXT NOT NULL,
  file_hash TEXT NOT NULL,
  file_size INTEGER,
  modified_at TEXT,
  imported_at TEXT NOT NULL,
  import_batch_id TEXT NOT NULL,
  UNIQUE(file_hash),
  FOREIGN KEY (source_id) REFERENCES import_sources(id),
  FOREIGN KEY (import_batch_id) REFERENCES import_batches(id)
);
```

Rule:
- Same file hash should not import twice unless user forces a reimport into a new batch with clear reason.

---

## 003_raw_runs.sql

Purpose:
- store normalized user score runs

```sql
CREATE TABLE raw_runs (
  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  platform TEXT NOT NULL,
  source_type TEXT NOT NULL,
  import_batch_id TEXT,
  imported_file_id TEXT,
  original_scenario_name TEXT NOT NULL,
  normalized_scenario_name TEXT,
  scenario_id TEXT,
  benchmark_definition_id TEXT,
  benchmark_version TEXT,
  score REAL NOT NULL,
  accuracy REAL,
  duration_seconds REAL,
  occurred_at TEXT,
  imported_at TEXT NOT NULL,
  setup_id TEXT,
  raw_payload_json TEXT,
  validation_status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'accepted',
  review_reason TEXT,
  duplicate_key TEXT,
  FOREIGN KEY (import_batch_id) REFERENCES import_batches(id),
  FOREIGN KEY (imported_file_id) REFERENCES imported_files(id)
);

CREATE INDEX idx_raw_runs_occurred_at ON raw_runs(occurred_at);
CREATE INDEX idx_raw_runs_scenario_id ON raw_runs(scenario_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_raw_runs_platform ON raw_runs(platform);
CREATE INDEX idx_raw_runs_duplicate_key ON raw_runs(duplicate_key);
```

Important:
- `raw_payload_json` stores useful original fields.
- Do not delete raw data when benchmark definitions update.
- Re-analysis should be possible.

