## 005_benchmark_definitions.sql

Purpose:
- source-first benchmark definition system

```sql
CREATE TABLE benchmark_definition_settings (
  definition_id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  version TEXT NOT NULL,
  source_type TEXT NOT NULL,
  source_name TEXT,
  source_url TEXT,
  installed_path TEXT,
  enabled INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,
  installed_at TEXT NOT NULL,
  last_checked_at TEXT,
  last_validated_at TEXT,
  validation_status TEXT NOT NULL,
  is_official_data INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0
);

CREATE TABLE benchmark_definition_cache (
  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  definition_id TEXT NOT NULL,
  version TEXT NOT NULL,
  definition_json TEXT NOT NULL,
  source_metadata_json TEXT NOT NULL,
  validation_result_json TEXT NOT NULL,
  cached_at TEXT NOT NULL,
  UNIQUE(definition_id, version)
);
```

Rule:
- Engine consumes validated normalized definitions.
- External source adapters feed this table/cache.

